  "doc_id": "44834",
  "text": "Thus the prion-like hypothesis of α-synuclein transmission in MSA has gained some support from both in vitro and in vivo studies. These models of oligodendrocyte α-synuclein accumulation dispense with the need for transcriptional upregulation of the protein and are thus more consistent with the current evidence from human studies of MSA brain tissue [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . However while potentially more valid on the basis of known pathogenesis, none of these models have so far achieved the phenotypic resemblance to true MSA described in the main transgenic animal models.",
